trend_summary: The peninsula evolves from partly cleared woodland with scattered dwellings to a fully built-out waterfront suburb. Central earthworks give way to a finished street grid, clusters of detached houses and cul-de-sacs. Shoreline dock space lengthens, raising impervious cover. After construction, vegetation rebounds around lots, but overall built surface and marina infrastructure steadily increase.
notable_changes: Central bare sand/excavation area replaced by a completed residential subdivision with multiple new streets.
Significant increase in the number and length of private docks and marina slips along west and south shores.
Tree canopy cleared for construction in early frame, followed by partial regrowth and landscaping in later years.
Addition of a new sports field or open recreational ground at the northern tip of the peninsula.
